  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustaining Resiliency Actions in Islands Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Continuous running of Climate-resiliency Field School and the Climate Information Services in the island municipalities;
-Development of a computer application tool that for agriculture livelihoods advisory services
-Assistance to LGU&#x2019;s local climate change action planning or review;
-Assistance to LGU in securing adaptation financing climate actions including those identified by communities;
-Generating lessons from our own Island Resilience work and Learning from Others</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. To sustain the resiliency work in the vulnerable communities of the 2 island municipalities; 
2. To assist 2 island LGUs in their vulnerability risk assessment and in the formulation and/or review of their local climate change action plans;
3. To enhance climate services/early warning provisioning 
4. To document and generate lessons on island resilience work</narrative>
  </description>
